10/12/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- A court in Vlora decided on Thursday (December 9th) to extradite Albino Prudentino to Italian justice authorities, who accuse him of a series of illegal activities linked to the Sacra Corona Unita mafia organisation.
Prudentino said the court procedures have been accompanied by human rights violations and accepted extradition to prove his innocence.
He was arrested on September 29th in Vlora, where he owns a number of properties.
(Balkan Web, Shekulli, VoA, Alsat - 09/12/10)Theme:
Rule of Law/Judicial efficiency Issue:
Albania/Italian mafia
